                  </hi>. I am an oilman, of Queen's-buildings, Knigbtsbridge—the prisoner was in my service, to obtain orders and collect money, which he should enter in a book, and pay to me or my foreman, who would sign the book for each sum—this "Joseph Ward" on these bills of Mrs. Wherry are the prisoner's writing—they are for 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 16<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on 2nd Aug., 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 17<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on 23rd Aug., and 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 16<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on 13th Sept.—I received this bill from Mrs. Mealing for 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 9 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>., on 5th July—this "Received, J. Ward" is the prisoner's writing—there is no receipt of money from Mrs. Mealing entered in the book that day—he did not pay me that or these of 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 0 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>. and 3<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 9 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>. from Mrs. Mealing on the same day—here is in the book 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. instead of 18<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
               <p>
